{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PqgyKiLaAvCua3tDPzsKYv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"package\", \"liberty:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0104f7ae-f5c0-40fd-9bc3-defb423c56be","uuid":"2f8eb54f-5e55-44ee-9640-533dcf4705dd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014d2RXjXRzYvpc7uEhuPu4x","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package jakarta.tutorial.order.ejb;\n    13→\n    14→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    15→import jakarta.annotation.PreDestroy;\n    16→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n    17→import jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\n    18→import jakarta.ejb.Startup;\n    19→\n    20→/**\n    21→ *\n    22→ * @author ian\n    23→ */\n    24→@Singleton\n    25→@Startup\n    26→public class ConfigBean {\n    27→\n    28→    @EJB\n    29→    private RequestBean request;\n    30→\n    31→    @PostConstruct\n    32→    public void createData() {\n    33→        request.createPart(\"1234-5678-01\", 1, \"ABC PART\",\n    34→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    35→        request.createPart(\"9876-4321-02\", 2, \"DEF PART\",\n    36→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    37→        request.createPart(\"5456-6789-03\", 3, \"GHI PART\",\n    38→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    39→        request.createPart(\"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, \"XYZ PART\",\n    40→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    41→        request.createPart(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"BOM PART\",\n    42→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    43→\n    44→        request.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7,\n    45→                \"1234-5678-01\", 1);\n    46→        request.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7,\n    47→                \"9876-4321-02\", 2);\n    48→        request.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7,\n    49→                \"5456-6789-03\", 3);\n    50→        request.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7,\n    51→                \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5);\n    52→\n    53→        request.createVendor(100, \"WidgetCorp\",\n    54→                \"111 Main St., Anytown, KY 99999\", \"Mr. Jones\",\n    55→                \"888-777-9999\");\n    56→        request.createVendor(200, \"Gadget, Inc.\",\n    57→                \"123 State St., Sometown, MI 88888\", \"Mrs. Smith\",\n    58→                \"866-345-6789\");\n    59→\n    60→        request.createVendorPart(\"1234-5678-01\", 1,\n    61→                \"PART1\", 100.00, 100);\n    62→        request.createVendorPart(\"9876-4321-02\", 2,\n    63→                \"PART2\", 10.44, 200);\n    64→        request.createVendorPart(\"5456-6789-03\", 3,\n    65→                \"PART3\", 76.23, 200);\n    66→        request.createVendorPart(\"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5,\n    67→                \"PART4\", 55.19, 100);\n    68→        request.createVendorPart(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7,\n    69→                \"PART5\", 345.87, 100);\n    70→\n    71→        Integer orderId = 1111;\n    72→        request.createOrder(orderId, 'N', 10,\n    73→                \"333 New Court, New City, CA 90000\");\n    74→        request.addLineItem(orderId, \"1234-5678-01\", 1, 3);\n    75→        request.addLineItem(orderId, \"9876-4321-02\", 2, 5);\n    76→        request.addLineItem(orderId, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, 7);\n    77→\n    78→        orderId = 4312;\n    79→        request.createOrder(orderId, 'N', 0,\n    80→                \"333 New Court, New City, CA 90000\");\n    81→        request.addLineItem(orderId, \"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, 1);\n    82→        request.addLineItem(orderId, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, 3);\n    83→        request.addLineItem(orderId, \"1234-5678-01\", 1, 15);\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    @PreDestroy\n    87→    public void deleteData() {\n    88→        \n    89→    }\n    90→}\n    91→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0104f7ae-f5c0-40fd-9bc3-defb423c56be","uuid":"ac6f238b-5190-4fd3-af0f-e36d5869183f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RTKi2ap138muZFbKBkfNz5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package jakarta.tutorial.order.ejb;\n    13→\n    14→import java.io.Serializable;\n    15→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    16→import java.util.Collection;\n    17→import java.util.Iterator;\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    20→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    21→\n    22→import jakarta.ejb.EJBException;\n    23→import jakarta.ejb.Stateful;\n    24→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    25→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    26→import jakarta.tutorial.order.entity.CustomerOrder;\n    27→import jakarta.tutorial.order.entity.LineItem;\n    28→import jakarta.tutorial.order.entity.Part;\n    29→import jakarta.tutorial.order.entity.PartKey;\n    30→import jakarta.tutorial.order.entity.Vendor;\n    31→import jakarta.tutorial.order.entity.VendorPart;\n    32→\n    33→\n    34→@Stateful\n    35→public class RequestBean {\n    36→    \n    37→    @PersistenceContext\n    38→    private EntityManager em;\n    39→\n    40→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(\"order.ejb.RequestBean\");\n    41→    \n    42→    public void createPart(String partNumber,\n    43→            int revision,\n    44→            String description,\n    45→            java.util.Date revisionDate,\n    46→            String specification,\n    47→            Serializable drawing) {\n    48→        try {\n    49→            Part part = new Part(partNumber,\n    50→                    revision,\n    51→                    description,\n    52→                    revisionDate,\n    53→                    specification,\n    54→                    drawing);\n    55→            logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Created part {0}-{1}\", new Object[]{partNumber, revision});\n    56→            em.persist(part);\n    57→            logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Persisted part {0}-{1}\", new Object[]{partNumber, revision});\n    58→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n    59→            throw new EJBException(ex.getMessage());\n    60→        }\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    public List<Part> getAllParts() {\n    64→        List<Part> parts = (List<Part>) em.createNamedQuery(\"findAllParts\").getResultList();\n    65→        return parts;\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    public void addPartToBillOfMaterial(String bomPartNumber,\n    69→            int bomRevision,\n    70→            String partNumber,\n    71→            int revision) {\n    72→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"BOM part number: {0}\", bomPartNumber);\n    73→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"BOM revision: {0}\", bomRevision);\n    74→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Part number: {0}\", partNumber);\n    75→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Part revision: {0}\", revision);\n    76→        try {\n    77→            PartKey bomKey = new PartKey();\n    78→            bomKey.setPartNumber(bomPartNumber);\n    79→            bomKey.setRevision(bomRevision);\n    80→            \n    81→            Part bom = em.find(Part.class, bomKey);\n    82→            logger.log(Level.INFO, \"BOM Part found: {0}\", bom.getPartNumber());\n    83→            \n    84→            PartKey partKey = new PartKey();\n    85→            partKey.setPartNumber(partNumber);\n    86→            partKey.setRevision(revision);\n    87→            \n    88→            Part part = em.find(Part.class, partKey);\n    89→            logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Part found: {0}\", part.getPartNumber());\n    90→            bom.getParts().add(part);\n    91→            part.setBomPart(bom);\n    92→        } catch (EJBException e) {\n    93→        }\n    94→    }\n    95→    \n    96→    public void createVendor(int vendorId,\n    97→            String name,\n    98→            String address,\n    99→            String contact,\n   100→            String phone) {\n   101→        try {\n   102→            Vendor vendor = new Vendor(vendorId, name, address, contact, phone);\n   103→            em.persist(vendor);\n   104→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   105→            throw new EJBException(e);\n   106→        }\n   107→    }\n   108→    \n   109→    public void createVendorPart(String partNumber,\n   110→            int revision,\n   111→            String description,\n   112→            double price,\n   113→            int vendorId) {\n   114→        try {\n   115→            PartKey pkey = new PartKey();\n   116→            pkey.setPartNumber(partNumber);\n   117→            pkey.setRevision(revision);\n   118→            \n   119→            Part part = em.find(Part.class, pkey);\n   120→            \n   121→            VendorPart vendorPart = new VendorPart(description, price, part);\n   122→            em.persist(vendorPart);\n   123→            \n   124→            Vendor vendor = em.find(Vendor.class, vendorId);\n   125→            vendor.addVendorPart(vendorPart);\n   126→            vendorPart.setVendor(vendor);\n   127→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   128→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   129→        }\n   130→    }\n   131→    \n   132→    public void createOrder(Integer orderId, char status, int discount, String shipmentInfo) {\n   133→        try {\n   134→            CustomerOrder order = new CustomerOrder(orderId, status, discount, shipmentInfo);\n   135→            em.persist(order);\n   136→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   137→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   138→        }\n   139→    }\n   140→\n   141→    public List<CustomerOrder> getOrders() {\n   142→        try {\n   143→            return (List<CustomerOrder>) em.createNamedQuery(\"findAllOrders\").getResultList();\n   144→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   145→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   146→        }\n   147→    }\n   148→    \n   149→    public void addLineItem(Integer orderId, String partNumber, int revision, int quantity) {\n   150→        try {\n   151→            CustomerOrder order = em.find(CustomerOrder.class, orderId);\n   152→            logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Found order ID {0}\", orderId);\n   153→            \n   154→            PartKey pkey = new PartKey();\n   155→            pkey.setPartNumber(partNumber);\n   156→            pkey.setRevision(revision);\n   157→            \n   158→            Part part = em.find(Part.class, pkey);\n   159→            \n   160→            LineItem lineItem = new LineItem(order, quantity, part.getVendorPart());\n   161→            order.addLineItem(lineItem);\n   162→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   163→            logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Couldn''t add {0} to order ID {1}.\", new Object[]{partNumber, orderId});\n   164→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   165→        }\n   166→    }\n   167→    \n   168→    public double getBillOfMaterialPrice(String bomPartNumber, int bomRevision, String partNumber, int revision) {\n   169→        double price = 0.0;\n   170→        try {\n   171→            PartKey bomkey = new PartKey();\n   172→            bomkey.setPartNumber(bomPartNumber);\n   173→            bomkey.setRevision(bomRevision);\n   174→            \n   175→            Part bom = em.find(Part.class, bomkey);\n   176→            Collection<Part> parts = bom.getParts();\n   177→            for (Part part : parts) {\n   178→                VendorPart vendorPart = part.getVendorPart();\n   179→                price += vendorPart.getPrice();\n   180→            }\n   181→            \n   182→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   183→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   184→        }\n   185→        return price;\n   186→    }\n   187→    \n   188→    public double getOrderPrice(Integer orderId) {\n   189→        double price = 0.0;\n   190→        try {\n   191→            CustomerOrder order = em.find(CustomerOrder.class, orderId);\n   192→            price = order.calculateAmmount();\n   193→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   194→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   195→        }\n   196→        return price;\n   197→    }\n   198→    \n   199→    public void adjustOrderDiscount(int adjustment) {\n   200→        try {\n   201→            List orders = em.createNamedQuery(\n   202→                    \"findAllOrders\")\n   203→                    .getResultList();\n   204→            for (Iterator it = orders.iterator(); it.hasNext();) {\n   205→                CustomerOrder order = (CustomerOrder)it.next();\n   206→                int newDiscount = order.getDiscount() + adjustment;\n   207→                order.setDiscount((newDiscount > 0)? newDiscount : 0);\n   208→            }\n   209→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   210→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   211→        }\n   212→    }\n   213→    \n   214→    public Double getAvgPrice() {\n   215→        try {\n   216→            return (Double) em.createNamedQuery(\n   217→                    \"findAverageVendorPartPrice\")\n   218→                    .getSingleResult();\n   219→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   220→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   221→        }\n   222→    }\n   223→    \n   224→    public Double getTotalPricePerVendor(int vendorId) {\n   225→        try {\n   226→            return (Double) em.createNamedQuery(\n   227→                    \"findTotalVendorPartPricePerVendor\")\n   228→                    .setParameter(\"id\", vendorId)\n   229→                    .getSingleResult();\n   230→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   231→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   232→        }\n   233→    }\n   234→    \n   235→    public List<String> locateVendorsByPartialName(String name) {\n   236→        \n   237→        List<String> names = new ArrayList<>();\n   238→        try {\n   239→            List vendors = em.createNamedQuery(\n   240→                    \"findVendorsByPartialName\")\n   241→                    .setParameter(\"name\", name)\n   242→                    .getResultList();\n   243→            for (Iterator iterator = vendors.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {\n   244→                Vendor vendor = (Vendor)iterator.next();\n   245→                names.add(vendor.getName());\n   246→            }\n   247→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   248→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   249→        }\n   250→        return names;\n   251→    }\n   252→    \n   253→    public int countAllItems() {\n   254→        int count = 0;\n   255→        try {\n   256→            count = em.createNamedQuery(\n   257→                    \"findAllLineItems\")\n   258→                    .getResultList()\n   259→                    .size();\n   260→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   261→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   262→        }\n   263→        return count;\n   264→    }\n   265→\n   266→    public List<LineItem> getLineItems(int orderId) {\n   267→        try {\n   268→            return em.createNamedQuery(\"findLineItemsByOrderId\")\n   269→                    .setParameter(\"orderId\", orderId)\n   270→                    .getResultList();\n   271→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   272→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   273→        }\n   274→    }\n   275→    \n   276→    public void removeOrder(Integer orderId) {\n   277→        try {\n   278→            CustomerOrder order = em.find(CustomerOrder.class, orderId);\n   279→            em.remove(order);\n   280→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   281→            throw new EJBException(e.getMessage());\n   282→        }\n   283→    }\n   284→    \n   285→    public String reportVendorsByOrder(Integer orderId) {\n   286→        StringBuilder report = new StringBuilder();\n   287→        try {\n   288→            List vendors = em.createNamedQuery(\n   289→                    \"findVendorByOrder\")\n   290→                    .setParameter(\"id\", orderId)\n   291→                    .getResultList();\n   292→            for (Iterator iterator = vendors.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {\n   293→                Vendor vendor = (Vendor)iterator.next();\n   294→                report.append(vendor.getVendorId()).append(' ')\n   295→                .append(vendor.getName()).append(' ')\n   296→                .append(vendor.getContact()).append('\\n');\n   297→            }\n   298→            \n   299→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   300→            throw new EJBException(e);\n   301→        }\n   302→        return report.toString();\n   303→    }\n   304→}\n   305→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0104f7ae-f5c0-40fd-9bc3-defb423c56be","uuid":"0b1e03f6-7e5d-4476-836d-030b484e431d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012oRsv1xa5AoFkz7caWbupU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package jakarta.tutorial.order.entity;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    15→import java.util.Collection;\n    16→import java.util.Date;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.persistence.CascadeType;\n    19→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    20→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    21→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    22→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    24→import jakarta.persistence.Temporal;\n    25→import jakarta.persistence.TemporalType;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.Transient;\n    27→\n    28→@Entity\n    29→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_CUSTOMERORDER\")\n    30→@NamedQuery(\n    31→    name=\"findAllOrders\",\n    32→    query=\"SELECT co FROM CustomerOrder co \" +\n    33→          \"ORDER BY co.orderId\"\n    34→)\n    35→public class CustomerOrder implements java.io.Serializable {\n    36→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 6582105865012174694L;\n    37→    private Integer orderId;\n    38→    private char status;\n    39→    private Date lastUpdate;\n    40→    private int discount;\n    41→    private String shipmentInfo;\n    42→    private Collection<LineItem> lineItems;\n    43→    \n    44→    public CustomerOrder() {\n    45→        this.lastUpdate = new Date();\n    46→        this.lineItems = new ArrayList<>();\n    47→    }\n    48→    \n    49→    public CustomerOrder(Integer orderId, char status, int discount, \n    50→            String shipmentInfo) {\n    51→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    52→        this.status = status;\n    53→        this.discount = discount;\n    54→        this.shipmentInfo = shipmentInfo;\n    55→        this.lastUpdate = new Date();\n    56→        this.lineItems = new ArrayList<>();\n    57→    }\n    58→    \n    59→    @Id\n    60→    public Integer getOrderId() {\n    61→        return orderId;\n    62→    }\n    63→    \n    64→    public void setOrderId(Integer orderId) {\n    65→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    66→    }\n    67→    \n    68→    public char getStatus() {\n    69→        return status;\n    70→    }\n    71→    \n    72→    public void setStatus(char status) {\n    73→        this.status = status;\n    74→    }\n    75→    \n    76→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    77→    public Date getLastUpdate() {\n    78→        return lastUpdate;\n    79→    }\n    80→    \n    81→    public void setLastUpdate(Date lastUpdate) {\n    82→        this.lastUpdate = lastUpdate;\n    83→    }\n    84→    \n    85→    public int getDiscount() {\n    86→        return discount;\n    87→    }\n    88→    \n    89→    public void setDiscount(int discount) {\n    90→        this.discount = discount;\n    91→    }\n    92→    \n    93→    public String getShipmentInfo() {\n    94→        return shipmentInfo;\n    95→    }\n    96→    \n    97→    public void setShipmentInfo(String shipmentInfo) {\n    98→        this.shipmentInfo = shipmentInfo;\n    99→    }\n   100→    \n   101→    @OneToMany(cascade=CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy=\"customerOrder\")\n   102→    public Collection<LineItem> getLineItems() {\n   103→        return lineItems;\n   104→    }\n   105→    \n   106→    public void setLineItems(Collection<LineItem> lineItems) {\n   107→        this.lineItems = lineItems;\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    public double calculateAmmount() {\n   111→        double ammount = 0;\n   112→        Collection<LineItem> items = getLineItems();\n   113→        for (LineItem item : items) {\n   114→            VendorPart part = item.getVendorPart();\n   115→            ammount += part.getPrice() * item.getQuantity();\n   116→        }\n   117→        return (ammount * (100 - getDiscount()))/100;\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    public void addLineItem(LineItem lineItem) {\n   121→        this.getLineItems().add(lineItem);\n   122→    }\n   123→    \n   124→    @Transient\n   125→    public int getNextId() {\n   126→        return this.lineItems.size() + 1;\n   127→    }\n   128→}\n   129→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0104f7ae-f5c0-40fd-9bc3-defb423c56be","uuid":"1830136f-baf3-4ce3-85e4-6a06e1ab73c0"}
