{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BsWS7ai1xXguxmtEnr7XoF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→body {\n    13→    background-color: #ffffff;\n    14→    font-size: 12px;\n    15→    font-family: Verdana, \"Verdana CE\",  Arial, \"Arial CE\", \"Lucida Grande CE\", lucida, \"Helvetica CE\", sans-serif;\n    16→    color: #000000;  \n    17→    margin: 10px;\n    18→}\n    19→\n    20→h1 {\n    21→    font-family: Arial, \"Arial CE\", \"Lucida Grande CE\", lucida, \"Helvetica CE\", sans-serif;\n    22→    border-bottom: 1px solid #AFAFAF; \n    23→    font-size:  16px;\n    24→    font-weight: bold;\n    25→    margin: 0px;\n    26→    padding: 0px;\n    27→    color: #D20005;\n    28→}\n    29→\n    30→a:link, a:visited {\n    31→  color: #045491;\n    32→  font-weight : bold;\n    33→  text-decoration: none;\n    34→}\n    35→\n    36→a:link:hover, a:visited:hover  {\n    37→  color: #045491;\n    38→  font-weight : bold;\n    39→  text-decoration : underline;\n    40→}\n    41→\n    42→th {\n    43→    font-weight: bold;\n    44→    text-align: center;\n    45→}\n    46→\n    47→td {\n    48→    text-align: center;\n    49→}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0104f7ae-f5c0-40fd-9bc3-defb423c56be","uuid":"1caf4a0c-2a43-4b2e-9fa1-59f5259004f9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Vu5LgyMZb3uuPxGg5BxveY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the migration. This is a Jakarta EE 10 application using:\n- **Jakarta EJB** (Stateful, Singleton, Startup)\n- **Jakarta JPA** (Entities with complex relationships, named queries)\n- **Jakarta JSF** (Faces/Facelets UI)\n- **Jakarta CDI** (@Named, @SessionScoped, @EJB, @Inject)\n- **Open Liberty** application server\n- **H2** in-memory database\n\nThe migration target is **Spring Boot** with:\n- Spring Data JPA (replacing JPA EntityManager + named queries)\n- Spring MVC REST controllers (replacing JSF/EJB)\n- Spring Boot auto-configuration (replacing Open Liberty)\n- Thymeleaf or simple REST endpoints (replacing JSF views)\n\nSince the original app is a JSF-based UI app, the most pragmatic Spring migration is to expose REST API endpoints that cover the same business logic (orders, parts, vendors, line items), use Spring Data JPA for persistence, and replace the JSF/EJB layer with Spring services and controllers.\n\nLet me begin the migration:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6334,"cache_read_input_tokens":43740,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6334,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":712},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0104f7ae-f5c0-40fd-9bc3-defb423c56be","uuid":"b23b9159-28c2-4440-9d85-05bd47bfa527"}
